A vintage-style illustration of an enormous filing cabinet made of dark mahogany wood stretching impossibly tall into a moody amber sky, with hundreds of tiny drawers slightly ajar, each spilling cascading streams of paper envelopes and sealed documents that transform mid-air into glowing digital particles. A lone figure in 1940s detective attire stands at the base, using a magnifying glass to examine one floating envelope caught between its physical and digital states. The scene evokes a film noir atmosphere with dramatic shadows, sepia tones, and art deco geometric patterns framing the edges, suggesting the tension between preservation and investigation of corporate secrets across time.
